  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Expensive comfort clothing - bathrobes and slippers, snuggle blankets, rubber crocs, etc. You wouldn't think it'd be so in-demand, but some of this stuff is worth more than the people wearing it. Rule #32 of surviving Night City (and also Zombieland) - enjoy the little things.</p><ul><li><p>While this outfit is being worn, the wearer suffers a <strong>-2 penalty to Wardrobe &amp; Styl</strong>e checks.</p></li><li><p>If the wearer is taking downtime to naturally heal (E.G. without use of a cryotank or other such measures), the wearer <strong>heals for an additional point of HP per day</strong> spent.</p></li><li><p>Once a week when the user spends a full day wearing this outfit, they <strong>gain 1 point of humanity</strong>. This bonus cannot be conferred more than once/week (E.G. through multiple outfits).</p></li></ul>"
    },
